":"2023-12-08T16:00:00+11:00","dateModified":"2026-04-01T13:36:41+11:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Pork-Belly-Fried-Rice.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-AU","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#breadcrumb"}},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/author/nicole/","name":"Nicole","url":"https://simplehomeedit.com/author/nicole/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/be03698f6c5f391b9911700916f3c22f08aa56fff6435a33329df2a9f3cab3a0?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/be03698f6c5f391b9911700916f3c22f08aa56fff6435a33329df2a9f3cab3a0?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Nicole","inLanguage":"en-AU"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Pork Belly Fried Rice Recipe | Simple Home Edit","keywords":"pork belly fried rice recipe","datePublished":"2023-12-08T16:00:00+11:00","dateModified":"2026-04-01T13:36:41+11:00","articleSection":"20 Minutes or Less, Dairy-free, Fakeaway, Family Favourites, Freezer-friendly, Get-ahead Meal Prep, Lunch, One-Pot, Pork, Sides","author":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/author/nicole/","name":"Nicole"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/#person"},"description":"Pork Belly Fried Rice is made with crispy pieces of pork belly (which take minutes to cook!) which are then stir-fried with garlic and ginger, delicious!","name":"Pork Belly Fried Rice Recipe | Simple Home Edit","@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Pork-Belly-Fried-Rice.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-AU","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#webpage"}},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Pork Belly Fried Rice","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Nicole"},"description":"This Pork Belly Fried Rice recipe is a fast and easy alternative to takeout that doesn\u2019t skimp on flavour! It\u2019s the perfect meal for busy weeknights.","datePublished":"2023-12-08T16:00:00+00:00","image":["https://simplehomeedit.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/12/Pork-Belly-Fried-Rice-3.webp"],"recipeYield":["4"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT10M","totalTime":"PT20M","recipeIngredient":["1 tbsp cooking oil (see note 1)","400 g pork belly rashers, skin cut off, cut into small pieces (approximately 2 cm/\u00be inch)","1 tsp sea salt flakes, plus extra to taste","1 tbsp freshly minced garlic","1 tsp freshly minced ginger","1  bunch bok choy, thickly sliced","4  eggs, whisked","555 g cooked, cold jasmine rice, or any rice of choice (see note 2 for freshly cooked rice)","2  spring onions (scallions), finely sliced, plus extra to garnish","1 tbsp Shaoxing wine or mirin (optional)","1 tsp dark soy sauce","2 tbsp tamari or all-purpose soy sauce","1 tbsp sesame oil","Freshly cracked black pepper, to taste","1 tsp toasted sesame seeds","2 tbsp kimchi (optional)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Cook the pork \u2013 Heat the cooking oil in a large, deep, heavy-based pan over high heat. Add the pork belly and salt and cook for 5\u20136 minutes until it becomes golden and crispy. Remove from the heat and set aside on a plate. Remove any excess pork fat from the pan, but leave 1 tablespoon.\u00a0\u00a0","name":"Cook the pork \u2013 Heat the cooking oil in a large, deep, heavy-based pan over high heat. Add the pork belly and salt and cook for 5\u20136 minutes until it becomes golden and crispy. Remove from the heat and set aside on a plate. Remove any excess pork fat from the pan, but leave 1 tablespoon.\u00a0\u00a0","url":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#wprm-recipe-12032-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the veggies \u2013 To the same pan, add the garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds. Stir through the sliced bok choy.","name":"Add the veggies \u2013 To the same pan, add the garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds. Stir through the sliced bok choy.","url":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#wprm-recipe-12032-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the egg \u2013 Push the veggies to the side of the pan and add the whisked egg. Cook for 1\u20132 minutes until firm and then stir with the bok choy to combine.\u00a0","name":"Add the egg \u2013 Push the veggies to the side of the pan and add the whisked egg. Cook for 1\u20132 minutes until firm and then stir with the bok choy to combine.\u00a0","url":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#wprm-recipe-12032-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Combine everything and add the flavourings \u2013 Return the cooked pork to the pan, along with the cooked, cold rice (see note 2 if using freshly cooked rice), spring onion, Shaoxing wine or mirin, dark soy sauce, tamari or soy sauce and sesame oil. Toss to combine.\u00a0","name":"Combine everything and add the flavourings \u2013 Return the cooked pork to the pan, along with the cooked, cold rice (see note 2 if using freshly cooked rice), spring onion, Shaoxing wine or mirin, dark soy sauce, tamari or soy sauce and sesame oil. Toss to combine.\u00a0","url":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#wprm-recipe-12032-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Serve \u2013 Season to taste and serve topped with extra sliced spring onion, toasted sesame seeds and kimchi on the side, if using.","name":"Serve \u2013 Season to taste and serve topped with extra sliced spring onion, toasted sesame seeds and kimchi on the side, if using.","url":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#wprm-recipe-12032-step-0-4"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"4","reviewCount":"4"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Really nice! I used some cabbage instead of bok choy as it's what I had in the fridge, and I wasn't prepared enough with cold rice so used the microwave packet of jasmine rice. Worked really well!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Becky"},"datePublished":"2026-05-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was a hit with the family the first time in made it,  cooking again tonight!!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Samantha"},"datePublished":"2026-04-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"My family loves it. Quick and easy as promised :)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Lucia"},"datePublished":"2025-03-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Absolutely delicious and pretty easy to cook for mid week. I made the rice in the morning to refrigerate and then added it back in when I cooked the rest for dinner. Will be adding to our rotation!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Katrina"},"datePublished":"2024-07-23"}],"recipeCategory":["dinner","entr\u00e9e","fried rice","Main Course","pork"],"recipeCuisine":["Chinese"],"keywords":"fried rice recipe, pork belly fried rice, pork fried rice","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"897 kcal","sugarContent":"3 g","sodiumContent":"1589 mg","fatContent":"68 g","saturatedFatContent":"22 g","transFatContent":"0.04 g","carbohydrateContent":"47 g","fiberContent":"3 g","proteinContent":"24 g","cholesterolContent":"236 mg","unsaturatedFatContent":"41 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#recipe","mainEntityOfPage":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#webpage","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://simplehomeedit.com/recipe/pork-belly-fried-rice/#richSnippet"}}]}</script>
