Ur2joDO0myOxOCAGACKxI3KW0r-ICEU6sAkA&amp;oe=6A49C175&quot;,&quot;640&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/scontent-syd2-1.cdninstagram.com\/v\/t51.82787-15\/732560533_18149478418503528_555466618083738434_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=111&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=18de74&amp;efg=eyJlZmdfdGFnIjoiQ0FST1VTRUxfSVRFTS5iZXN0X2ltYWdlX3VybGdlbi5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=Ui-I9ZYDV8cQ7kNvwEPnq6b&amp;_nc_oc=AdpK0Z5rG88oI6pqJq3vHGJvHgf2xf6Rb_O5leYdzI2q21s0PFzqLqlprbn2Fxf6Pw0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-syd2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;edm=ANo9K5cEAAAA&amp;_nc_gid=K9RnyEUxnSaCPJOYU85rYQ&amp;_nc_tpa=Q5bMBQGOKLIQXyLzKONnK5AOk3KqmCdlZ_zAbvYfVtWtlW2ZEuURZNMHN2GYP20vhQtJOdbHnGm8EuL8MA&amp;oh=00_AQBFg8qOMrUr2joDO0myOxOCAGACKxI3KW0r-ICEU6sAkA&amp;oe=6A49C175&quot;}"
		   tabindex="-1">
			<img width="1000" height="560" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201000%20560'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="The biggest savings in our house rarely come from choosing the cheapest ingredients. They come from choosing dinners that actually make sense for real life.
Recipes that use supermarket ingredients. Meals that don’t require buying three different sauces you’ll never use again. Dinners that make use of what you already have sitting in the fridge.

Because when dinner feels complicated, expensive or overwhelming, that’s usually when takeaway starts looking very appealing. 😅

These are five dinners under $20 that my family loves. They’re simple, satisfying and realistic enough for busy weeknights when nobody has the energy for anything fancy.

Here’s what’s on the menu:
• Chicken Rissoles
• Drunken Noodles
• Stuffed Pita Arayes
• Creamy Chicken Noodle Soup
• Korean Beef Rice Bowls

Simple ingredients. Less food waste. Fewer specialty products. More dinners that actually get made.
That’s the sweet spot for me. ❤️

Find the recipes on my website via the link in bio, or comment RECIPE and I’ll send you the links to all of these.

